    <etym xml:lang="ru">По всей вероятности, кавказское слово; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="av"
                ><lang/><w>cʼcʼahil</w><gloss><q>серый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="av"><w/><gloss><q>голубой</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="tab"
                ><lang/><w>cʼux-</w><gloss><q>серый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼaxi</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                    ><w>cʼaka</w><gloss><q>сыворотка</q></gloss></mentioned>, („серая жидкость“, ср.
            <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>cʼæx
            syly</w><gloss><q>сыворотка</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                ><lang/><w>śʼexw</w><gloss><q>синий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>голубой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                ><w>śʼxo</w><gloss><q>серый</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Намечаются связи и на
        иранской почве: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>zaǧ</w><gloss><q>синий</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>zaǧ-časm</w><gloss><q>синеглазый</q></gloss></mentioned>). Старым
        иранским словом для понятия ‘серый’ было в осетинском %ixær%i-, которое сохранилось в <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_xæræg"/> ‘осел’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xærīs"/> ‘ива’,
        д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæræ"/> %imeǧæ%i ‘серый туман’. Для ‘синего’ или
        ‘темно-серого’ существовало слово %iæxsm%i. Совмещение в одном (слове значений ‘серого’,
        ‘синего’ и ‘зеленого’ объясняется хозяйственной неактуальностью этих цветовых различий в
        условиях староосетинского быта. В аналогичных условиях такой же цветовой „синкретизм“
        наблюдается в других языках; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                    ><lang/><w>á-ec˳ʼa</w><gloss><q>серый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ab"><w/><gloss><q>синий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>зеленый</q></gloss></mentioned>, .</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">From all appearances, it is a Caucasian word; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="av"
                ><lang/><w>cʼcʼahil</w><gloss><q>gray</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="av"><w/><gloss><q>light blue</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="tab"><lang/><w>cʼux-</w><gloss><q>gray</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼaxi</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                    ><w>cʼaka</w><gloss><q>serum</q></gloss></mentioned>, (“gray liquid”, cf.
            <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>cʼæx
        syly</w><gloss><q>serum</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                ><lang/><w>śʼexw</w><gloss><q>dark blue</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kbd"><w/><gloss><q>light blue</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kbd"><w>śʼxo</w><gloss><q>gray</q></gloss></mentioned>, . There are also
        connections in Iranian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>zaǧ</w><gloss><q>blue</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>zaǧ-časm</w><gloss><q>blue-eyed</q></gloss></mentioned>). The
        word %ixær%i- which is now found in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæræg"/> ‘donkey’, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_xærīs"/> ‘willow’, Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæræ"/>
        %imeǧæ%i ‘gray fog’ was an old Iranian word for ‘gray’. For ‘blue’ or ‘dark gray’ there was
        the word %iæxsin%i. Combining meanings ‘gray’, ‘blue’ and ‘green’ in one word is explained
        by the economic irrelevance of these colour differences in the conditions of old Ossetian
        life. The same colour “syncretism” in analogous conditions is found in other languages; cf.
            <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
            ><lang/><w>á-ec˳ʼa</w><gloss><q>gray</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>blue</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>green</q></gloss></mentioned>, .</etym>
</entry>
